name: Samambaia.1
description:
This fern is native in Brazil, it are an epiphytic plant (not a parasitic), that is, it only uses other plants as support so it can reach the sun, without taking any water or nutrients - it roots embrace the host plant! 

ID: Migrogramma squamulosa | Family: Polypodiaceae
